<HEADLINE> European Stocks Fall </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- European stock exchanges closed lower across the  
continent Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Major indexes in London, Paris, Frankfurt and Milan all dropped  
more than 1 percent and Madrid's IBEX-35, the biggest loser, fell 
1.9 percent. 
</P>
<P>
	The drops were led by banks and oil stocks.  
</P>
<P>
	Spain's biggest bank, Banco Santander Central Hispano, ended  
down 2.4 percent while the Bank of Scotland was down 3.6 percent. 
Among oil stocks, Paris-listed TotalFina fell 2.4 percent, while 
Elf Acquitaine dropped 3 percent. 
</P>
<P>
	The Dow Jones Stoxx Index of 594 European companies closed down  
5.06 points, or 1.6 percent, at 316.36, while the Dow Jones Euro 
Stoxx Index, which tracks 295 companies in countries that joined 
the euro, ended down 4.79 points at 332.71. 
</P>
<P>
	The Dow Jones Euro Stoxx 50 Index ended down 56.83 points at  
3,905.52, while the DJ Stoxx 50 Index closed down 60.92 points at 
3,843.39. 
</P>
<P>
	Frankfurt's Xetra DAX index closed down 1.4 percent. The Paris  
CAC 40 index finished 1.5 percent lower, and Milan's MIBtel index 
fell 1.6 percent. 
</P>
<P>
	London's FTSE 100 index ended down 1.5 percent.  

</P>
</TEXT>
