<HEADLINE> Northwestern QB Transfers to Penn </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	EVANSTON, Ill. (AP) -- Gavin Hoffman, Northwestern's starting  
quarterback last season as a redshirt freshman, is transferring to 
the University of Pennsylvania, the university announced. 
</P>
<P>
	Hoffman completed 176 of his 323 pass attempts for 3,199 yards  
and 13 touchdowns a year ago. 
</P>
<P>
	Because Hoffman is transferring to a Division I-AA school, he  
will be eligible to play immediately for the Quakers. 
</P>
<P>
	``We wish him nothing but the best,'' Wildcats head coach Randy  
Walker said Tuesday. 
  	   	
