<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Kids Plead Innocent in Killing Plot </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PORT HURON, Mich. (AP) -- Two 14-year-old boys have pleaded  
innocent to charges of plotting a massacre at their middle school. 
</P>
<P>
	Justin Schnepp and Jedaiah Zinzo were arraigned yesterday on  
charges of conspiracy to commit first-degree murder. 
</P>
<P>
	Schnepp and Zinzo, who will be tried as adults, could face life  
in prison if convicted. Their trial is scheduled for Nov. 16. 
</P>
<P>
	Two 13-year-olds, Daniel Fick and Jonathan McDonald, have also  
pleaded innocent to conspiracy charges in the case. Their trial is 
scheduled for Sept. 8, but prosecutors say they may request that 
all four be tried together. 
</P>
<P>
	Witnesses testified during preliminary hearings that the teens  
were plotting to stage a robbery to obtain firearms, then seize the 
school office, use the public address system to call an assembly in 
the gym and massacre students and teachers. 
</P>
<P>
	Authorities said they foiled the plot after classmates reported  
it to school officials. 
</P>
<P>
	The boys remain in custody in the St. Clair County Juvenile  
Center on $100,000 cash bond. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
