<HEADLINE> Clinton Cheers Fugitive's Capture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MIAMI BEACH, Fla. (AP) -- President Clinton saluted law  
enforcement officials and said ``all Americans can rest easier'' 
after Tuesday's arrest of Rafael Resendez-Ramirez, the suspect in 
the railroad murders. 
</P>
<P>
	The president, on a daylong visit to Florida, issued a written  
statement after Resendez-Ramirez, suspected in eight killings, 
surrendered in El Paso, Texas. 
</P>
<P>
	``I want to thank all of the state, local and federal law  
enforcement officials whose hard work led to the surrender of the 
suspected `railway killer' earlier today,'' the president said. 
</P>
<P>
	``As a result of their determined efforts and the cooperation of  
Mexican authorities, the suspect is now in custody in the United 
States,'' the president said. ``All Americans can rest easier 
knowing that law enforcement authorities will bring the full force 
of the law to bear in this case.'' 
</P>
</TEXT>
