<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Japan Stocks Rise in Early Trading / Japanese Stocks  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TOKYO (AP) -- The dollar slipped against the yen early Wednesday,  
while Japanese stocks rose moderately amid expectations for Japan's 
economic recovery. 
</P>
<P>
	The dollar bought 121.34 yen in early trading, down 0.80 yen  
from late Tuesday in Tokyo but slightly above its late New York 
level of 121.32 yen. 
</P>
<P>
	The benchmark 225-issue Nikkei Stock Average gained 63.81  
points, or 0.35 percent, to 18,244.90 in the first 30 minutes of 
trading. On Tuesday, the average closed down 0.42 points, or 0.03 
percent. 
</P>
<P>
	In currency dealings, the dollar moved marginally from its late  
New York level in the absence of fresh market-moving news. 
</P>
<P>
	Traders said the market still held some fear of another round of  
Bank of Japan dollar-buying intervention, which could stem the 
greenback's slide. 
</P>
<P>
	In recent weeks, the Bank of Japan intervened to stop the yen's  
rise against the dollar, an action seen taken to help the country's 
economy recover from its worst recession since World War II. 
</P>
<P>
	In other currencies, the euro was traded at 123.30 yen, down  
from 123.64 yen late Tuesday in Tokyo. 
</P>
<P>
	On the stock market, share prices opened modestly higher on some  
hopes that Japan's economy will continue to recover. 
</P>
<P>
	On Tuesday, the Economic Planning Agency said in its latest  
monthly report that the nation's economy is improving somewhat, 
with private consumption recovering and the effects of government 
support steps sinking in. 
</P>
<P>
	In New York on Tuesday, the Dow Jones industrial average fell  
25.96 points to 11,175.02. 
</P>
<P>
	The broader Tokyo Stock Price Index of all issues listed on the  
first section was up 5.56 points, or 0.37 percent, to 1,489.25. The 
TOPIX closed down 0.42 points, or 0.03 percent, the day before. 
</P>
<P>
	The yield on the benchmark 10-year Japanese government bond rose  
to 1.6250 percent from Tuesday's finish of 1.6000 percent, driving 
its price down to 101.52 yen from 101.74 yen. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
