<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> United States 2, Derby County 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DENVER (AP) -- Eddie Lewis and Ben Olsen scored in the second  
half to give the U.S. men's soccer team a 2-1 victory over Derby 
County Club of the English Premier League on Tuesday night. 
</P>
<P>
	Olsen broke a 1-1 tie in the 76th minute, sending a perfectly  
timed header past goalkeeper Mart Pool from 18 feet out. Lewis had 
tied the game in the 64th minute, scoring on a rebound after a shot 
by Ernie Stewart was blocked. 
</P>
<P>
	Dean Sturridge scored the only goal for Derby County, which is  
using an 11-day tour of the United States to get in shape for its 
1999-2000 season, which begins Aug. 7. 
</P>
<P>
	Derby County hit two crossbars and a goal post in the second  
half. 
</P>
<P>
	Derby County led 1-0 at the half on Sturridge's goal in the 26th  
minute. Sturridge ran a give-and-go play with Darryl Powell and 
sent the return pass over goalkeeper Brad Friedel's left shoulder 
from 15 feet out. 
</P>
<P>
	Paul Bravo had a good scoring chance moments after Sturridge's  
goal, but Pool made a diving stop of the 20-foot shot. 
</P>
<P>
	It was the U.S. team's final tuneup for the Confederation Cup,  
which runs July 24-Aug. 4 in Mexico. 
</P>
</TEXT>
