<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Newsmagazines, Movies Top Nielsens / TV Ratings  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Newsmagazines and movies -- instead of  
previously-seen comedies and dramas -- were popular summertime fare 
for network television viewers last week. 
</P>
<P>
	The Tuesday edition of ``Dateline NBC,'' which featured a story  
on a woman accused of attacking her husband, was the week's 
top-rated program. CBS' ``60 Minutes'' narrowly came in second. 
</P>
<P>
	Four newsmagazines and three movies filled Nielsen Media  
Research's top 10. ABC's Monday movie, ``She Woke Up Pregnant,'' 
topped the feature film chart. 
</P>
<P>
	CBS won the week with a 6.6 rating and 13 share. NBC was second  
with a 5.8 rating and 11 share, ABC had a 5.7 rating and 11 share 
and Fox was at 4.4 and 9. The WB had a 2.3 rating and 4 share, UPN 
had a 1.4 rating and 3 share and Pax TV was at 0.7 and 1. 
</P>
<P>
	The WB was heartened by the ratings for its new comedy, ``Movie  
Stars.'' It scored the highest rating for the network in its Sunday 
time slot since last October. 
</P>
<P>
	Meanwhile, the poor ratings for back-to-back episodes of  
``Suddenly Susan'' on July 5 had to depress NBC: The two shows had 
fewer viewers than anything else last week on ABC, CBS or NBC. 
``Suddenly Susan'' is coming back next fall in revamped form. In 
NBC's defense, Monday was a holiday for many viewers. 
</P>
<P>
	NBC's ``Nightly News'' won the evening news competition with a  
6.8 rating and 16 share. ABC's ``World News Tonight'' had a 6.7 
rating and 16 share, while the ``CBS Evening News'' was at 5.9 and 
14. 
</P>
<P>
	A rating point represents 994,000 households, or 1 percent of  
the nation's estimated 99.4 million TV homes. The share is the 
percentage of in-use televisions tuned to a given show. 
</P>
<P>
	For the week of July 5-11, the top 10 shows, their networks and  
ratings were: ``Dateline NBC-Tuesday,'' NBC, 9.3; ``60 Minutes,'' 
CBS, 9.2; ``Frasier,'' NBC, 8.7; ``ABC Monday Night Movie: She Woke 
Up Pregnant,'' ABC, 8.5; ``Will &AMP; Grace,'' NBC, 8.4; 
``20/20-Friday,'' ABC; 8.0; ``CBS Sunday Movie: Streets of Laredo, 
Part 1,'' CBS, 8.0; ``CBS Wednesday Movie: A Perfect World,'' CBS, 
7.9; ``Friends,'' NBC, 7.9; ``60 Minutes II,'' CBS, 7.8. 


  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
