<HEADLINE> Dow Drops 85 in Early Trading / Wall Street Report  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- The Dow Jones industrial average is down 85  
points in today's early going. Losers on the New York Stock 
Exchange hold a 2-1 lead over decliners. 
</P>
<P>
	The Nasdaq Composite Index is down 28 points and the S&AMP;P 500  
Index is down nine points. 
</P>
<P>
	Analysts expected that stocks would give ground at the open,  
following the overseas markets lower. 
</P>
<P>
	The focus today is on second quarter earnings, with the early  
reports from several companies coming in better than analysts had 
expected. 
</P>
<P>
	Investors are also keeping a close eye on South America,  
wondering if the economic problems in Argentina are going to 
spread. 
  	   	
</P>
