<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-13 12:31:00 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE>  China Welcomes Soccer Team Home </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BEIJING (AP) -- President Jiang Zemin led an official welcoming  
ceremony Tuesday for the Chinese women's soccer team, which brought 
home a World Cup silver medal. 
</P>
<P>
	The 5-4 loss to the United States on overtime penalty kicks in a  
politically charged match chagrined Chinese fans. But their sorrow 
has been tempered by pride that China's women made it to the finals 
and held the Americans scoreless in regular play. 
</P>
<P>
	``You didn't disappoint the wishes of the masses,'' Jiang told  
the team during a reception at the Great Hall of the People in the 
center of Beijing. ``You showed on the playing field the 
self-reliance and self-confidence of Chinese women.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The team returned Monday night from the United States to a  
raucous welcome by hundreds of fans who beat drums, crashed cymbals 
and sang the Chinese national anthem outside Beijing airport. 
</P>
<P>
	Also at the ceremony Tuesday were Communist Party leaders Li  
Peng, Li Ruihuan, Hu Jintao and Wei Jianxing. 
</P>
<P>
	Many Chinese had looked on the World Cup final in Pasadena,  
Calif., as a grudge match against a rival with whom China has a 
range of political and trade disputes. 
</P>
<P>
	Jiang said he hoped the women's soccer team and other Chinese  
athletes made ``persistent efforts'' to win other honors for the 
country. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW19990713.0241 </DOCNO>
