<HEADLINE> Periodicals To Get Postal Refunds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Publishers of nonprofit periodicals are  
eligible for refunds for mailings over the last seven months in 
which they were overcharged, the Postal Service's board of 
governors has ruled. 
</P>
<P>
	The situation was created when some periodicals paid a higher  
postage rate at the nonprofit rate than they would have paid at the 
regular rate. 
</P>
<P>
	The Postal Service filed a proposal in April that would allow  
nonprofits to request a refund. But the agency said the effective 
date for refunds would have been April, instead of January -- the 
date the rates first took effect. 
</P>
<P>
	The National Federation of Nonprofits and the Advertising Mail  
Marketing Association had objected to the April refund date. The 
Postal Service's board of governors ruled on Monday. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
