<HEADLINE> Sparky Anderson in Hospital for Tests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DETROIT (AP) -- Former Detroit Tigers and Cincinnati Reds manager  
Sparky Anderson was hospitalized today for testing, including 
checks of heart function. 
</P>
<P>
	Anderson, 65, lives in Thousand Oaks, Calif., but was visiting  
here to play in a golf tournament, according to his friend, Dan 
Ewald. He was taken to Henry Ford Hospital on Monday night. 
</P>
<P>
	``He was not feeling well. They're running tests on him. They  
are checking his heart,'' said Ewald, adding that Anderson had felt 
under the weather for more than a week. 
</P>
<P>
	Anderson managed the Reds from 1970-78, winning championships in  
1975-76. He then managed the Tigers for 17 years, resigning after 
the 1995 season with a team-record 1,331 victories and a World 
Championship in 1984. 
  	   	
</P>
