<HEADLINE> Uruguay 5, Chile 3 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ASUNCION, Paraguay, (AP) -- Chile blew two penalty kicks, one in  
regulation and another in the tiebreaker, and Uruguay qualified for 
the final of the Copa America soccer tournament with a 5-3 victory 
in the penalty-kick shootout after a 1-1 tie Tuesday night. 
</P>
<P>
	Playing with the assurance of a veteran, Uruguay's 20-year-old  
goalie, Fabian Cabrini, dived to his left to knock away the kick by 
Mauricio Aros in the shootout. Chile didn't miss again, but Uruguay 
didn't miss at all. 
</P>
<P>
	The victory was virtually a repeat of Uruguay's 1-1 defeat of  
Paraguay in the quarterfinals, when Carini also made a big save in 
the tiebreaker. 
</P>
<P>
	Uruguay, which brought a junior team to the Copa America, faces  
the winner of the Brazil-Mexico matchup in the final. Again 
Uruguary will be the underdog, but its youngsters already have 
shown they can play with the best. 
</P>
<P>
	Uruguay took a 1-0 lead after a corner kick in the 22nd minute.  
Walter Coelho fired the ball to the far post and Lembo caught the 
defense flatfooted to head it in. 
</P>
<P>
	Paraguayan referee Ubaldo Aquino awarded a penalty that went for  
naught when Chile's Salas bounced a shot off the crossbar. 
</P>
<P>
	Chile tied it 1-1 in the 60th minute on Zamorano's soaring  
header. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
